==English==
===Etymology===
Probably reminiscent of the detailed description of a [[fight]] or [[boxing]] match, with [[blow]] in the sense of a hit or strike.

===Noun===
'''[[blow]]-[[by]]-blow'''
#{{idiom}} An [[account]], [[description]], or [[commentary]] including every [[action]] or [[event]].
#:''The media published a '''blow-by-blow''' of the trial as it happened.''

===Adjective===
'''blow-by-blow'''
#{{idiom}} Detailing every action or event completely.
#:''He gave a '''blow-by-blow''' account of the entire trip.''